    INTRO_CONST = {
        EQUIP_COMPOSE_INTRO = "#c000000Gear Fusion #n#r#r#r#r#r#c000000[Fusion]: #r#r#c5c5c5c1. Using the Fusion system, you can fuse #cff6b114 pieces of Legendary Gear at the same level#c5c5c5c to #t1#g868686#cffe0001 piece of Ultra Gear#c5c5c5c#t0. #rOnly Lv. #c5c5c5c#cff6b1140 and above gear #c5c5c5c can be fused.#r#c5c5c5cfused materials will be consumed, and you will get a random Ultra Gear of the same level. #r#c5c5c5cFusion produces Ultra Gear. The gear slot is determined by the slot of the gear used in Fusion.#r",
        FBSECRET_INTRO = "#c000000Agency Assessment Rules#n#r#r#r#r#r#c000000[Gameplay Rules]: #r#r#c5c5c5c1. Agency Assessments feature difficult and dynamic gameplay. Players can team up to take on challenges together. #r#c5c5c5cThe faster you complete an assessment, the more rewards you will get. As a result, it's recommended you challenge these with #cff6b113 players#c5c5c5c on your team.#r#r#c5c5c5c2. Agency Permits are required before you can take the assessment. #r#c5c5c5cAny player on the team can submit an Assessment Permit. #r#r#c5c5c5c3. Results for each round of the Agency Assessment are calculated every #cff6b11 Thursday and Sunday #c5c5c5c. #r#c5c5c5cRewards will be sent based upon who got the best results in each round. #r#c5c5c5cPlayers' Assessment Permits will be reset at the beginning of each round. #r#r#r#r#c000000[Assessment Permit]: #r#r#c5c5c5c1. The higher the Assessment Permit's level and floor, the more difficult the stage it activates. Complete harder stages to get more rewards. #r#c5c5c5cPermit Level: At the beginning of each round, your Agency Level determines your Permit Level. #r#c5c5c5cPermit Floor: At the beginning of each round, a permit's floor is reset to Floor 1. #r#r#c5c5c5c2. Use a permit to activate an assessment stage. Complete challenges to increase a permit's floor. #r#c5c5c5cFailing a challenge will break a permit. #cff6b11 After a permit is broken, it needs to be repaired #c5c5c5c before it can be used. #r#r#c5c5c5c3. Permit Level and Floor Overview #r#c868686Agency Level 01-29, Permit Level 20; Permit Floor 1-18 #r#c868686Agency Level 30-39, Permit Level 30; Permit Floor 1-18 #r#c868686Agency Level 40-49; Permit Level 40; Permit Floor 1-18 #r#c868686Agency Level 50-59, Permit Level 50; Permit Floor 1-21 #r#c868686Agency Level >=60, Permit Level 60; Permit Floor 1-21 #r#r#r#r#c000000[High-yield]: #r#r#c5c5c5c1. Use: While High-yield are in effect, the chances of getting legendary gear are increased upon completing a stage. #r#r#c5c5c5c2. How to acquire: Each time a round resets, you will get a certain number of High Rewards chances. #r#r#c5c5c5c3. Cost: Completing Level Bracket 10 and above assessment stages to spend High-yield Attempts.#r",
        GODBODY_INTRO = "#c000000Gear Rules #n#r#r#r#r#r#c000000[Enhance]: #r#r#c5c5c5c1. Enhancing gear will boost its base stats and Star Level stats. #r#c5c5c5cEnhancement level is bound to the gear's slot, and will remain even when changing gear.#r#r#c5c5c5c2. The higher an Agency's level, the higher the enhancement level limit. #r#r#r#r#c000000[Boost]: #r#r#c5c5c5c1. Boosting gear will increase its base stats. #r#c5c5c5cBoost star level is bound to the gear's slot, and will remain even when changing gear. #r#c5c5c5cEach piece of gear can only be boosted #cff6b11 5 times#c5c5c5c. Once a piece of gear has been boosted to 5 stars, it can be overclocked. #r#r#c5c5c5c2. Overclocking gear will increase its base stats and activate the corresponding Overclock affix. #r#c5c5c5cThe overclock star level is bound to the gear's slot and will remain even when changing gear. #r#c5c5c5cEach piece of gear can only be overclocked #cff6b11 3 times#c5c5c5c. Each time will activate 1 new affixes. #r#r#c5c5c5c3. The higher an Agency's level, the higher the limit. #r#r#r#r#c000000[Modification]: #r#r#c5c5c5c1. Modifying gear will increase its modification stats and progress. #r#c5c5c5cModification stats are bound to a gear's slot and will remain even when changing gear. #r#c5c5c5cThere is a chance to get a crit when modifying, which increases modification stats and progress by an additional amount. #r#r#c5c5c5c2. When modification progress is filled, modification rank will increase. #r#c5c5c5cReach a certain modification rank to get special stats. #r#r#c5c5c5c3. The higher a gear's star level, the higher its modification rank limit. #r#r#r#r#c000000[Fusion]: #r#r#c5c5c5c1. Under the Fusion system, gear that meets the following conditions can be fused into Ultra Gear.#r#c5c5c5cA: Gear is Lv. 40 or above#r#c5c5c5cB: Gear is Legendary#r#r#c5c5c5c2. In the Fusion system, gear that meets the following conditions can be fused into radiant gear.#r#c5c5c5cA: Gear is Lv. 60 or above#r#c5c5c5cB: Gear Rarity is golden or radiant#r#r#c5c5c5c3. Only gear of the same level and rarity can be fused.#r#c5c5c5cA: 4 pieces of legendary gear can be fused into 1 piece of Ultra Gear (with a chance to acquire a set).#r#c5c5c5cB: 4 pieces of Ultra Gear can be fused into 1 piece of radiant gear (with a chance to acquire a set).#r#c5c5c5cC: 2 pieces of radiant gear can be fused into 1 piece of radiant gear (guaranteed to acquire a set).#r#r#c5c5c5c4. The gear slot of acquired gear will be determined by the gear slot of gear fused. #r#r#r#r#c000000[Transfer]: #r#r#c5c5c5c1. Gear that has extra stats can transfer these extra stats. #r#c5c5c5cOnly different gear of the same slot can transfer extra stats. #r#c5c5c5cYou can only transfer extra stats from unequipped gear to equipped gear. #r#c5c5c5cYou cannot move extra stats from a high-level piece of gear to a low-level one. #r#r#c5c5c5c2. Each piece of gear can only have 1 extra stats of the same type. #r#c5c5c5cextra stats will not add a new stat to a piece of gear if there is already a stat of the same type. It will simply replace that stat. #r#c5c5c5cExtra stats smaller than stats of the same type already on the target gear will not be able to transfer.#r",
        HOME_COMFORT_INTRO = "#c000000Mood Recovery #n#r#r#r#r#r#c000000[Mood Recovery Rules]: #r#r#c5c5c5c1. After a character enters the dorm, they will gradually recover their Mood. #r#c5c5c5cThe first time a character enters the dorm, their initial Mood will default to full. #r#r#c5c5c5c2. The higher a dorm's Comfort, the more quickly the hero staying there will recover their Mood. #r#c5c5c5cArrange furniture and complete furniture sets to increase a dorm's Comfort. #r#r#r#r#c000000[Losing Mood]: #r#r#c5c5c5c1. Mood will be consumed when a character carries out commissions. #r#r#c5c5c5c2. Characters cannot recover Mood while carrying out commissions. They can only recover Mood once the quest is finished. #r#r#r#r#c000000[Comfort and Mood Recovery Chart]: #r#r#c5c5c5c1000 Comfort+12 Mood/h#r#r#c5c5c5c1500 Comfort+17 Mood/h#r#r#c5c5c5c2000 Comfort+20 Mood/h#r#r#c5c5c5c3000 Comfort+27 Mood/h#r#r#c5c5c5c4000 Comfort+32 Mood/h#r#r#c5c5c5c5000 Comfort+37 Mood/h#r",
